TC-007 – Access shopping cart after adding a product

Preconditions: User is on the products page.

Steps:

1. Select a product.
2. Click the "Add to cart" button.
3. Click the shopping cart icon at the top of the page.

Expected Result:
The system should redirect the user to the shopping cart page and display the added product.

Actual Result:
The system redirected the user to the shopping cart page and displayed the added product.

Status: Passed.

TC-008 – Add product to cart

Preconditions: User is on the products page.

Steps:

1. Select a product.
2. Click the "Add to cart" button.

Expected Result:
The product should be added to the cart, the button should change from "Add to cart" to "Remove", and the cart icon should display the number of added products.

Actual Result:
The product was successfully added to the cart.

Status: Passed.

TC-009 – Remove product from cart

Preconditions: User has at least one product in the cart.

Steps:

1. Access the shopping cart page.
2. Locate the added product.
3. Click the "Remove" button.

Expected Result:
The product should be removed from the cart and should no longer be displayed.

Actual Result:
The product was successfully removed.

Status: Passed. 

TC-010 – Validate product sorting by lowest price

Preconditions: User is on the products page.

Steps:

1. Locate the product sorting dropdown.
2. Click on the sorting dropdown.
3. Select the option "Price (low to high)".

Expected Result:
All products should be reordered from the lowest price to the highest price.

Actual Result:
The products were displayed in ascending price order.

Status: Passed.

TC-011 – Validate product sorting by highest price

Preconditions: User is on the products page.

Steps:

1. Locate the product sorting dropdown.
2. Click on the sorting dropdown.
3. Select the option "Price (high to low)".

Expected Result:
All products should be reordered from the highest price to the lowest price.

Actual Result:
The products were displayed in descending price order.

Status: Passed.

TC-012 – Validate checkout with empty required fields

Preconditions: User has a product in the shopping cart.

Steps:

1. Click the "Checkout" button.
2. Leave all required fields empty (First Name, Last Name, and Zip/Postal Code).
3. Click the "Continue" button.

Expected Result:
The system should display a message informing that the required fields must be filled and prevent the user from continuing.

Actual Result:
The system displayed the message "Error: First Name is required" and did not allow the user to continue.

Status: Passed.

